      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and blind bake the case",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub together {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}}, {{sea-salt-fine}}, and {{unsalted-butter}} until it resembles fine crumbs. Mix {{egg-yolks}} with {{water}} and add just enough to bring the dough together. Chill for 30 minutes. Heat the oven to 190°C fan. Roll to 3 mm, line a 23 cm tart tin, prick the base, blind bake with beans for 15 minutes, remove beans and bake for a further 10 to 12 minutes until the base is deep golden and completely dry. Cool in the tin. Reduce the oven to 150°C fan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the custard",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the {{egg-yolks}} egg yolks, {{eggs}} whole egg, and {{caster-sugar}} until combined but not frothy. Warm the {{double-cream}} and {{whole-milk}} with the {{vanilla-bean-paste}} in a saucepan until barely simmering. Pour slowly over the egg mixture, whisking constantly. Strain through a sieve into a jug.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour and bake, 35 to 40 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Place the tart tin on the oven shelf. Pour the custard into the blind-baked case, do this in the oven to avoid spilling as you carry it. Grate {{nutmeg-whole}} fresh nutmeg liberally over the surface. Bake at 150°C fan for 35 to 40 minutes, propping the oven door open with a wooden spoon to keep the temperature even. The tart is done when the outer 4 to 5 cm is set and the centre wobbles as one mass when nudged. Remove from the oven and cool in the tin for at least 1 hour before removing. Serve at room temperature, not cold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
